page.title: 11Plant Life in Summer
page.content: In June we saw a blaze of :_ Dandelions, Buttercups,Lesser stitchwort, Bugle, Intermediate deadnettle, Daisies, Dog's mercury, Thistles, Nettles and Goosegrass. In July we identified these plants:_ Cow parsley, Hogweed, Soft hawksbeard, Herb Robert, Plantain, Dead nettle, Forget-me-not, Field Scabious, Hedge parsley, Hedge bedstraw, Red and white campion, Lesser yellow trefoil, Speedwell, White and pink clover, Scarce willowherb, Meadow cranesbill, Great knapweed, Nipple-wort, Shepherd's purse, Common agrimony, Black mustard and Wild cabbage. Grasses included- Oat grass and Squirrel tailed fescue. Late July and August- Poppies grew amongst the wheat and Rosebay Willowherb abounded in the hedges.
